# Alert Levels
[bold][color=#008000]GREEN[/color] - No threat or passive threat to the station.[/bold]
- Search warrants must be approved by a Magistrate or a Captain.
- Department search warrants are forbidden, but can still be approved by the Captain or the relevant Head of Staff; however a letter must be sent to CC.

- More lenient uniforms for all departments:
- Medical staff must wear something identifiable.
- Security does not have to wear body armour or helmets, however should still be identifiable. The officer’s lethal sidearm will always be permitted.
- Security Officers are not permitted to wear heavy armour or carry longarms under normal circumstances. 
- Officers should always attempt to follow de-escalation procedures.

- Triage goes in order or most life threatening conditions to least.
- “Medical Staff > Staff with the most life threatening conditions.”


[bold][color=#1e90ff]BLUE[/color] - There is a potential threat to the station and its crew.[/bold]
- The crew should report suspicious activity to security.
- Search warrants may be approved by the HoS.
- Department search Warrants may be approved by the Magistrate, Commanding Officer or the respective Head of Department.

- Slightly stricter uniform standards:
- Security officers must not wear any other department uniforms that would cause confusion.
- Officers are advised to wear body armour and their helmet.
- Security Officers must carry their designated lethal sidearm.
- Security Officers may be equipped with heavy armour and longarms at the discretion of the Head of Security.

- Medical triage should focus on the treatment of Command and Security;
- “Medical Staff > Command Staff > Security Staff > Staff with the most life threatening conditions.”


[bold][color=#cd7f32]BRONZE[/color] - Dangerous Fauna on Station.[/bold]
- Search warrants must be approved by a Magistrate or a Commanding Officer, provided that the Commanding Officer is not also acting as the Head of Security, in which the approval of warrants will fall to the Executive Officer.
- Department search warrants are forbidden, but can still be approved by a Commanding Officer or Magistrate; however a fax must be sent to CC.

- Security Officers must not wear any other department uniforms that would cause confusion.
- Security is authorized to equip longarms and heavy armour. Security must wear their body armour or a hardsuit. Security may wear their helmets. 
- Security must carry a lethal sidearm or at least one other type of lethal weapon.
- Security may request entry into departmental areas to eliminate hostile fauna.
- Crew are legally obligated to comply with any and all orders from Security forces involving the elimination of hostile fauna. 

This alert level is intended for use surrounding the presence of dangerous fauna such as spiders, snakes, slimes, etc. 

[bold][color=#ffbf00]AMBER[/color] - There is an active threat to the station.[/bold]
- All crew members are advised to stay within their departments unless otherwise evacuated.
- Random searches are permitted. 
- The HoS may approve Departmental Searches.
- Security must wear two identifiable pieces of clothing at all times, and are not allowed to wear other department clothing that could cause confusion.
- Security is advised to be armed with longarms and heavy armour.
- Security must wear body armour or a hardsuit.
- Security must carry a designated lethal sidearm or other lethal weapon.

- Medical staff must wear multiple articles of identifiable clothing.
- Medical triage should focus on the treatment of Command and Security;
- “Medical Staff > Command Staff > Security Staff > Staff with the most life threatening conditions.”

For something like an active gunman still at large. Threatening to the crew, and should be dealt with as soon as possible. Not an imminent threat to the entire station.

[bold][color=#ff0000]RED[/color] - There is an imminent threat to the station.[/bold]
- All crew must stay within their departments, unless otherwise evacuated.
- Head of Security and the Commanding Officer are elevated equally in the chain of command.

- The Commanding Officer must secure the nuclear authentication disk.
- The Commanding Officer must possess the red telephone at all times, maintain a clear line of communication with Central Command.

- The crew is required to listen to orders by Security Officers. 
- Random searches are permitted. 
- All officers are allowed to enter and search any area. 
- Officers are allowed to have all access. 
- The station’s armory should be made open to all Security Officers.
- Security must wear two identifiable pieces of clothing at all times, and are not allowed to wear other department clothing that could cause confusion.
- Security must wear body armour or a hardsuit. May wear their helmet.
- Security must carry a lethal sidearm or any other lethal weapon.

- Medical staff must wear multiple articles of identifiable clothing.
- Medical triage should focus on the treatment of Command and Security;
- “Medical Staff > Command Staff > Security Staff > Staff with the most life threatening conditions.”


[bold][color=#8b0000]DELTA[/color] - There is an imminent threat of destruction to the station.[/bold]
- All crew must proceed to evacuate the station.
- If evacuation is not possible the crew must prevent the destruction of the station at all costs.
- The Commanding Officer must secure the nuclear authentication disk.
- The Commanding Officer must possess the red telephone at all times, maintain a clear line of communication with Central Command.

- Security must wear two identifiable pieces of clothing at all times, and are not allowed to wear other department clothing that could cause confusion.
- Security Officers are required to be armed with longarms and heavy armour.
- Security must carry their lethal sidearm or any other lethal weapon.
- Crew are permitted to be armed as an auxiliary force in order to assist Security, armed crew must accompany an officer at all times.

- Medical staff must wear multiple articles of identifiable clothing.
- Medical triage should focus on the treatment of Command and Security;
- “Medical Staff > HoS and Captain > Security > Armed Crew > Unarmed Command Staff > Unarmed Crew”

The Nuclear Fission Device has been armed, the crew has 300 seconds to disarm the device or evacuate the station.

[bold][color=#db7093]GAMMA[/color] - Extreme threat that has damaged security operational abilities. ERT will arrive. To relieve the station.[/bold]
- This alert level is only accessible by CC, and can be called upon through the red phone.
- All remaining crew should work together and gather as many weapons as possible. All crew should hold out and survive by any means necessary.
- Any remaining security officers should attempt to guide numbers of crew to a safe area.
- All crew will listen to any ERT orders.
- Any items used for survival are permitted while still in danger.

Station security forces have been made unable to actually prevent a major threat to the station, and all hope of domestic resistance has been completely crushed. At this stage it is evacuation in some form, and survival, most laws will no longer matter.

[bold][color=#9400d3]EPSILON[/color] - Surprise NanoTrasen inspection.[/bold]
- NT authorised personnel hold absolute command over the station.
- Security Officers are not permitted to be armed.
- All crew are required to be at dress standard.
- All crew are required to present at a staging point.
- All command staff are required to organise the crew.

Glory to NanoTrasen.
